\begin_layout Standard
Maize is an important crop in Uganda, prioritized by the Government as a
 key contributor to household/national food and income security.
 Unfortunately, current maize farm yields are far below (more than 60%)
 what is achievable.
 This is largely attributed to farmers' slow uptake of high yielding crop
 varieties, despite a diversity of such varieties on the market.
 
